# MediaCore Providers

## Architecture

```
Provider
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Metadata
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Manifest
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Formats
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Download
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Thumbnail
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Subtitle
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Live
```

Implement `packages.core.provider.Provider` or extend `providers.base_module.PlatformModule`.

```python
capabilities = ProviderCapabilities(...)

def supports(self, url: str) -> bool: ...
def metadata(self, url: str) -> MediaMetadata: ...
def download(self, url: str, format_id: str, dest: Path) -> DownloadResult: ...
```

## Registration order

1. Working providers first (early list in `packages/registry/providers.py`)  
2. Catalog platform modules from `providers/platforms/factory.py` (skip if name already registered)  
3. `generic` + `example` last  

Batch upgrades: skill `mediacore-upgrade-loop` + `scripts/provider_upgrade_queue.py`.

Use `packages.registry.providers.reset_registry()` in tests after registry changes.

## Platform modules

- On disk: `providers/modules/<slug>/` (~1360 packages).
- Index: `providers/data/providers_index.json`.
- Host maps: `providers/platforms/hosts.py` ‚Üí `scripts/generate_providers.py`.
- Direct media URLs on a module's hosts: metadata + download via `PlatformModule`.
- Page/watch URLs: `status=not_configured` ‚Üí `ProviderNotConfiguredError` until official API.

## Do not

- Wire third-party scraper libraries for extract/download.
- Put platform scrape logic inside `packages/core`.
- Recreate `providers/stubs/` (renamed to `modules/`).
